        <p class="eyebrow">Our Story</p>
        <h2>From One Truck to 180+</h2>
        <p>Mike founded MNS1 Express in 2011 with a single truck in the Chicago suburbs. No investors, no fleet manager — just a driver who believed he could do it better.</p>
        <p>That one truck became two. Then ten. Then fifty. Each step was built on the same principle: treat drivers the way you'd want to be treated. Pay fairly. Keep your promises on home time. Run good equipment. Don't cut corners.</p>
        <p>In 2023, MNS1 moved to its current headquarters at 14458 S Depot Dr, Plainfield, IL 60544 — a purpose-built facility with room to grow. The fleet now runs 180+ trucks across 11 Midwest states, with a target of 500.</p>
        <p>Mike is still in the building. Not a figurehead — an operator. IT professional with 14+ years of infrastructure experience who brings that engineering mindset to every part of the business: systems, processes, decisions.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p>
        <h3>1% Better Every Day</h3>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li><strong>Always Forward</strong> Our brand is an arrow. We don't look back — we improve, adapt, and move. Every decision pushes us forward.</li>
          <li><strong>Driver-First Decisions</strong> Equipment, pay, home time, policies — we make choices from the driver's seat. If it doesn't work for drivers, it doesn't work for us.</li>
          <li><strong>The Explorer Archetype</strong> We're not the biggest. We're the ones willing to explore new territory — in technology, in operations, in how a carrier should treat its people.</li>
          <li><strong>No Shortcuts</strong> 180+ trucks built without cutting corners on safety, equipment, or people. The plan to 500 follows the same playbook.</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
